## Introduction
* Uses [Dremhel APOTHEOSIS 2.2.2f](https://www.drehmal.net/) for world.
* Based on [itzg/docker-minecraft-server](https://github.com/itzg/docker-minecraft-server)
* Uses Minecraft 1.20.1

## Assumptions
* You can already SSH into the SBC
* Your user can issue sudo commands on the SBC
* You already have docker installed and your user is part of the `docker` group

## Setup on Arm64 SBC
1. Clone this repo to desired location on SBC (e.g. `/opt/minecraft`), change ownership, create data directory

```
sudo git clone https://github.com/rstrube/minecraft-arm64-drehmal /opt/.
chown -R $USER:$USER /opt/minecraft-arm64-drehmal
mkdir -p /opt/minecraft-arm64-drehmal/data

```
2. Download latest [Dremhel APOTHEOSIS](https://www.drehmal.net/) world.zip file.

Note: because it's a Google Drive Link if your SBC doesn't have a web browser, download it on a PC and scp it to the SBC

```
scp Drehmal\ APOTHEOSIS\ 2.2.2f.zip user@sbc:/opt/minecraft-arm64-drehmal/.
```

3. Extract the world.zip file and rename it

```
cd /opt/minecraft-arm64-drehmal
unzip Drehmal_APOTHEOSIS_v2.2.2f.zip -d data/

# The extracted folder should become the world — rename if needed:
mv data/Drehmal* data/world
```

# Run via Docker Compose
The `docker-compose.yml` file has already been setup for some sane defaults for SBCs.  Feel free to tweak some of the parameters based on your specific SBC's hardware (CPUs & RAM).

```
docker compose up -d
```

# Server Side Mod Information
Drehmal recommends both server and client side modes.  Below is a list of mods that are package with this repository and match what Drehmal v2.2.2f recommends.

